                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to Mr. Wood, of Hyde-street, Bloomsbury. Between seven and eight o'clock in the morning, the prisoner pawned the coat for 12 s.</p>
               <p>WATKINS DETHERIDGE. I am an officer - I apprehended him, and took him to the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I intended to redeem it.</p>
